text: Fort Nonsense is a historic earthen fortification at Annapolis, Anne Arundel County, Maryland. It consists of two arcs of embankments and ditches that date at least to the early 19th century. It is located near on a hilltop which has remained undisturbed by the surrounding Annapolis Naval Ship Research and Development Center. It is the last vestige of Annapolis Harbor fortifications. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1984. ==References== ==External links== *, including photo from 1983, at Maryland Historical Trust Category:Military facilities on the National Register of Historic Places in Maryland Category:Buildings and structures in Annapolis, Maryland Category:National Register of Historic Places in Annapolis, Maryland
